			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>MAGICIAN TOP TEN </SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial?><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>1) Improve pet damage output (Pet Issues/Requests) </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial?></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>First and Foremost, the damage upgrades for pet focuses is, by far, inadequate. Pets do not receive even close to the damage increases that damage and mana foci provide, nor do they scale close in terms of overall melee increases. Additionally, there is a gap between equivalent Ornate-level magician pets, and Time-level magician pets, that Minion of Darkness does not bridge.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN> (new details submitted)</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>Please see reply for exact details (the boards only allow 20,000 characters per post)</FONT></SPAN><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>2) Overhaul class specific AA's. </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Here are the Mage AA’s that are in need of attention and the detail you requested on Elemental Agility:</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>This has been re-submitted with the details collected by Danille from this thread, </FONT><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=1496" target=_blank><SPAN red? **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=1496</FONT></SPAN></A></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;Please see reply for exact details (the boards only allow 20,000 characters per post)</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>3) Fix Fire pet </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Rytan has all details about fixing this pet. But to summarize:</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>One solution is to make it Warrior-class again.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>The other solution is to tweak the AI of the pet, as well as specific fixes:</SPAN></P>
<UL>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Nuke or melee only. If it has mana, it nukes and doesn't stop. </SPAN></DIV></LI>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Mana regen too slow. Its mana regen is abysmal. </SPAN></DIV></LI>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Too easy to unmezz mobs. When the pet starts to cast, it cannot be interrupted. </SPAN></DIV></LI>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Remove AOE’s. AOEs cause problems with aggro and mez breaks. </SPAN></DIV></LI>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Remove Debuffs. Often when it casts its various dispels it will take a debuff cast on the mob instead. </SPAN></DIV></LI>
<LI>
<DIV class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Pet appear with the buffs already on it when it is summoned. When the pet is summoned it wastes considerable time initially buffing itself instead of engaging in combat. </SPAN></DIV></LI>
<LI class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Remove any root/snare/cancel magic spells from a pet’s lineup which primarily makes a pet un-useable for groups and raids. Root causes shaky proximit aggro, snare is unreliable, and like said above the dispel causes problems.<BR><BR></SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN> (new details submitted)</SPAN></FONT><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>4) Improved Damage shield </SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial?><BR line-break? **SMURF**?mso-special-character:></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><BR><SPAN red? **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>This item was marked as done.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>These details have been resubmitted for re-evaluation</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><SPAN red? **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Please see reply for exact details (the boards only allow 20,000 characters per post)</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>5) Streamline the item summoning process (more target summons) </SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial?><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><BR>All summoned items should become targeted just like mod rods. <BR><BR></SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:>The current plan is to implement this change&nbsp;before Omens of War launches</SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>6) Allow suspended pets to zone, OR allow pets to remain with their master while the master is invisible.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>(Pet Issues/Requests) </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>While allowing pets to zone has been one of the biggest boosts in Magician power in&nbsp;years, its inherent flaw is that you still lose your pet to invisibility. Suspended Minion allowed you to keep your pet when you went invisible, but zoning still kills it. One solution is to just allow suspended pets to zone with their master. The other (perhaps more favorable) solution is to prevent pets from being destroyed by Invisibility. Since pets are Beta-Neutral faction, they will not aggro anything anyway.</SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial?></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>This item was marked as done.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>These details have been resubmitted for re-evaluation</FONT></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>7) Improve pet Heals. (Pet Issues/Requests) </SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><BR><BR>Pet heals need to be on-par with equivalent Beastlord heals HP-wise. The amount healed needs to be the same as beastlord heals, the cast time needs to be 3.75 seconds, and the recast time should be removed altogether<SPAN **SMURF**?COLOR: #004080?>.&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**?COLOR: black?>Higher level pet heals especially need a boost; in the time it takes to heal the pet, theres a high probability it is already dead. Also the amount currently healed is insufficient to&nbsp;equivalent level content (in Gates, for example, the 1200 HP healed from Planar Renewal is often less than one hit from random yard trash in Kod`Taz).<BR line-break? **SMURF**?mso-special-character:></SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN> (new details submitted)</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>8) Revamp pet focus availability. (Pet Issues/Requests)</SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?> <BR><BR>Add a Minion of Darkness focus in Tier 3 Planes of Power zones (ideal loot for mages would be First Sergeant's Insignia, and/or Orb of Infinite Terror) to help bridge the gap between equivalent Ornate-geared Magicians and Elemental-geared Mages, pet wise.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Put the *Mancy focuses in the game. This will help bridge the gap between Ornate/Vex Thal-geared Magicians, Elemental-geared magicians, and Time-geared Magicians.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN> (new details submitted)</SPAN></FONT><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>9) COH useable in more zones. (make CoTH available in all corpse summoning zones) </SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><BR><BR></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;><BR></SPAN><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt; Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt?>10) Better utility in groups and raids </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 13.5pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>a) Summoned snare pet weapons,&nbsp;and new proc weapons for the pet</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>b) Castable root as a form of crowd control</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>c) AE malosinia</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>d) Group CoH</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in none? **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>e) Cross-zone CoH (i think its being implemented)</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;f) Malos</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 12pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Arial?>This has been re-submitted with the details collected by Danille from this thread,</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? red; FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR:><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=1497" target=_blank><FONT color=#ff0000>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=1497</FONT></A></SPAN></P>
