<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">a) Increase the HP of Minion of Darkness to better fall between Summoner's Boon and Minion of Eternity</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Unfocused Air pet = 3775hp (approx), DPOC= 4200hp (approx), MoD needs to be 4600 (approx), MoE= 5085 (approx), Mancy = MoE.</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Furthermore, there does not exist a pet focus that bridges the gap between Vex Thal mages and Plane of Time mages. This gap should be fixed by introduing the "Mancy" line of focuses in the Elemental Planes. Pyromancy from Plane of Fire, Aeromancy from Plane of Air, Aquamancy from Plane of Water, Geomancy from Plane of Earth.<BR><BR **SMURF**"mso-special-character: line-break"><BR **SMURF**"mso-special-character: line-break"></SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">b) Upgrade the max melee damage of focused pets</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Using air pet as example:</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Summary:</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Unfocused - 83 damage, level 60&nbsp;<BR>Summoner's Boon (Ornate) - 86 damage,<SPAN **SMURF**"mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>level 61</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Minion of Darkness (Vex Thal) - 97 damage, level 62, needs a HP boost&nbsp;as described above.</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Minion of Eternity (Time) - 108 damage, level 63</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Ritual Summoning (Qvic)- 118 damage, level 64</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Minion of Discord (Tacvi) - 128 damage, level 65</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"><BR></SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Omens of War pets should scale in a similar manner.</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Increasing the maximum melee damage as said above will help ensure pets scale better with focii compared to equivalent level spell focii.</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">C) Upgrade the burnout series</SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">The haste components do not need to be looked at, it’s the other statistical boosts these buffs provide. In addition, Beastlords can augment their pet with a +75 dex proc buff, whereas Magicians cannot. Somewhere along the way, beastlords overpowered magicians in terms of buffing up the pet. This should be corrected.<BR><BR **SMURF**"mso-special-character: line-break"><BR **SMURF**"mso-special-character: line-break"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Burnout 3<BR>from 50 str, 13 ac<BR>to 55 str, 15 ac, 25 atk<BR>Burnout 4<BR>from 60 str, 16 ac<BR>to 30 ac, 40 atk, 75 dex<BR>Ancient Burnout Blaze<BR>to 100 str, 60 ac, 60 atk, 75 dex<BR>Burnout 5<BR>from 80 str, 40 atk, 22 ac<BR>to 115 str, 71 ac, 75 atk, 75 dex</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN **SMURF**"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"></SPAN></P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
