		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Top 10 list item #2 details<namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>1) Elemental Agility- This AA is broken.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Here is the description: (4 / 8 / 12 AA points needed to purchase this ability.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Increases Magician pet avoidance and mitigation by an approximate 2%, 5%, and 10%).</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Mages have purchased all three levels of this AA at a cost of 24 AA’s and have noticed no significant change in the pet’s mitigation performance. (Parses taken show that Elemental Agility 3 = 3% less mob accuracy. Mob accuracy goes from 66%ish to 63%ish. Also parsed a 1.5%-2% drop in dps taken by pet, from pre-EA to EA3. Please note that parses have an +/- 3% error factor on results so the pet performance benefit is negligible, if it works at all). This is probably the 2nd worst AA of all in GoD in terms of overall usefulness and cost vs. reward.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Link to old parsing info - http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13390</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>(Xalmat is conducting some new parses as we speak.)</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>2) Elemental Forms –</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>a) They need to be usable on a mount. Remove the illusion component, or allow the illusion component to be removed without losing the full benefit of the buffs.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>b) The levitate component from air form needs to be removed. There are many zones where levitation is not allowed and this currently causes the AA to fail.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;No changes planned at this time</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>3) Mass Group Buff –</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Mages have one group buff, our Damage Shield (duration 15 minutes). With a recast time of 1 hour and 12 minutes, this AA is virtually useless at present unless you give us a faster recast time or both quick MGB and Spell Casting Reinforcement AA’s. The problem is the 72-minute reuse time is far too long for a situational DS. (Currently, mages are toggling TGB/on and just casting group DS every 15 minutes anyway).</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>4) Quick MGB –</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Asked for this AA above and why don't all classes that have MGB have this?</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>Addition not being considered at this time.</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>5) Frenzied Burnout –</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Presently has a 72 minutes recast timer. It needs to be lower, on the margin of 9 minutes like a discipline. Or increase the duration to 72 minutes. Even throw in a hasted Frenzied, which reduces the reuse time of this ability by 25% per rank (on-par with hasted Mend).</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>6) Turn Summoned –</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>This AA is useless. It resists 90% of the time and no one ever uses it anyway because mages can’t snare. Mages all agree that the fear component needs to be removed, and it should be changed to a "Manaburn type" ability against summoned mobs, minus the draining of your mana pool (or alternatively just a very high DD with very low aggro).</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>7) Elemental Pact –</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>(eliminates the need for a regent to be used when making elemental pets, in our case malachite) Needs to remove the need to carry malachite, not just removing the cost. All classes who have this AA want to eliminate the need to carry one regent in their inventory as it takes up a slot that can be sued for something else.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>This is something coding will not allow at this time, however it is something that may be considered in the future as code allows</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>8) Host of the Elements –</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>a) The 5/7 and 9 tiny earth pets that are created when this AA is used, needs to be level 60 so they can enrage. They need more HP to match the Shaman version. AA cost needs to be lowered to </SPAN><namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><date Year="2003" Day="3" Month="3"><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>3/3/3</SPAN></date><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>. Reuse timer needs to be lowered to 9 minutes, not 22 minutes. Duration needs to be increased to 1 minute, not 30 seconds. </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0.25in?><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>b) In addition many mages would like the Host or the Elements AA to be able to summon tiny earth, air, water, fire and monster pets. Currently we only have one form that is available (earth).</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>9) Mend Companion -</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>As EQ content has grown and our pets have as well, this AA doesn't do anywhere near enough for the pet anymore. A maximum Mend does, at most, about 50% of the pet's HP, which is barely enough for one melee round in most high level zones (On a fully raid buffed Rathe's Son, this is usually around 25%). The AA is really insufficient if you're using a high HP pet like Rathe's Son, or if any of our 5 pets are focused and/or buffed.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;Dev notes - Mend Companion, like normal mend, is a percent based heal.&nbsp; It scales with the pet.&nbsp; Beyond that, if Mend won’t soak a single round of melee damage, then the problem isn’t in mend.&nbsp; Upgrading it means the pet lives an extra 3 seconds.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>10) Secondary Forte -</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>15 AAs for 2.5% mana preservation. The cost of our most commonly used nuke is Firebolt of Tallon, which costs 500 mana to cast (with no mana preservation items equipped). The mana savings for 15 AA’s comes to 12.5 mana saved. Considering the average lvl 65 mage has a 4500-mana pool, this AA provides a savings of 0.277% per nuke. This is probably the worst AA of all in GoD in terms of overall usefulness and cost vs. reward. At 15 AA’s, our suggestion is to increase the specialization level to 200.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;No changes planned at this time<BR>Dev notes - Any further decrease in mana cost is going to come at a premium and in small chunks.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>11) Shared Health -</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Should have much larger range and unlimited damage cap for the duration of the ability. Its rare Magicians and pets are close to each other because mages fight from a ranged position. In fact we often fight from a large distance. Reuse time should be 3 minutes to be equal with Warrior /shield, not 15 minutes. The range needs to be increased from 10 to 100 or more. Melee range for pets on many NPCs is often higher than /shield range.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>12) Elemental Alacrity -</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>VERY overpriced. It should be 3/3/3/3/3, not 3/6/9/12/15. Overall the AA cost on this is so high it’s prohibitive; maxing out our nuke crit AAs gives a better gain per AA than this. This AA should also apply to our pets nuking ability, not just melee. (Their nukes should be criting as well)</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>13) Healing Adept/Gift/Adv Adept/Adv Gift -</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>With the emphasis no longer on pet expendability but rather pet survival, it makes sense for Magicians to have these abilities now.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>14) Quick Damage -</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Why don't we have this? Without it, druids (a priest class) are actually out-nuking us consistently.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;<FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being considered as an addition with future expansions</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>15) Spell Casting Reinforcement/SCR Mastery -</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Why don't we have this? We have buffs just like anyone else</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>Addition not being considered at this time.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?><FONT color=#ff0000>Dev notes - They have a few buffs, but so do wizards and necromancers and they don’t have it either.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#000080><FONT face=Verdana></FONT></FONT></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>Possible new pet AA’s:</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>16) Pet Command Mastery-</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>This AA would give a mage additional control over their pets. Some nice features to have would be.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>a) Stick to one mob (regardless of low health from a second mob the pet would not switch targets)</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>To fix the issues we have with the fire pet:&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>b) Spell casting on/off</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>c) Melee on/off</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>17) Shared Attributes-</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY: Arial?>This AA would allow the pet to benefit from the gear that the master (mage) has equipped. The pet would gain specific melee and spell casting enhancements just like PC's do.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0.25in?><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P></DIV><p>Message Edited by Ashlanne on <span class=date_text>08-06-2004</span> <span class=time_text>04:51 PM</span>
