			<DIV><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 10.0pt? mso-bidi-font-size: Arial; 13.5pt;>&nbsp;
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>MAGICIAN TOP TEN <namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>1) Improve pet damage output (Pet Issues/Requests) </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>First and Foremost, the damage upgrades for pet focuses is, by far, inadequate. Pets do not receive even close to the damage increases that damage and mana foci provide, nor do they scale close in terms of overall melee increases. Additionally, there is a gap between equivalent Ornate-level magician pets, and Time-level magician pets, that Minion of Darkness does not bridge.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Please see reply for exact details (the boards only allow 20,000 characters per post) (See post on the Magician board for details)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><BR>2) Overhaul class specific AA's. </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Here are the Mage AA’s that are in need of attention and the detail you requested on Elemental Agility:</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Dev notes have been added (the boards only allow 20,000 characters per post) (See post above for details)</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>3) Fix Fire pet </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Rytan has all details about fixing this pet. But to summarize:</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>One solution is to make it Warrior-class again.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>The other solution is to tweak the AI of the pet, as well as specific fixes:</SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc>
<LI class=MsoNormal .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list: 0in COLOR: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Nuke or melee only. If it has mana, it nukes and doesn't stop. </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list: 0in COLOR: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Mana regen too slow. Its mana regen is abysmal. </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list: 0in COLOR: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Too easy to unmezz mobs. When the pet starts to cast, it cannot be interrupted. </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list: 0in COLOR: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Remove AOE’s. AOEs cause problems with aggro and mez breaks. </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list: 0in COLOR: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Remove Debuffs. Often when it casts its various dispels it will take a debuff cast on the mob instead. </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list: 0in COLOR: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Pet appear with the buffs already on it when it is summoned. When the pet is summoned it wastes considerable time initially buffing itself instead of engaging in combat. </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list: 0in COLOR: 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Remove any root/snare/cancel magic spells from a pet’s lineup which primarily makes a pet un-useable for groups and raids. Root causes shaky proximit aggro, snare is unreliable, and like said above the dispel causes problems.<BR><BR></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red; COLOR: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><BR><BR>4) Improved Damage shield <BR><BR></SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red; COLOR: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Currently being discussed</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></FONT></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Please see reply for exact details (the boards only allow 20,000 characters per post) (See post on the Magician board for details)</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><BR>5) Streamline the item summoning process (more target summons) <BR><BR>All summoned items should become targeted just like mod rods. <BR><BR></SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>The current plan is to implement this change&nbsp;before Omens of War launches</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><BR>6) Allow suspended pets to zone, OR allow pets to remain with their master while the master is invisible.&nbsp; (Pet Issues/Requests) </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>While allowing pets to zone has been one of the biggest boosts in Magician power in&nbsp;years, its inherent flaw is that you still lose your pet to invisibility. Suspended Minion allowed you to keep your pet when you went invisible, but zoning still kills it. One solution is to just allow suspended pets to zone with their master. The other (perhaps more favorable) solution is to prevent pets from being destroyed by Invisibility. Since pets are Beta-Neutral faction, they will not aggro anything anyway.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red; COLOR: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Dev notes - An AA that upgrades Suspend Minion to allow a suspended pet to zone is under consideration for a future expansion</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red; COLOR: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#cccccc></FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><BR>7) Improve pet Heals. (Pet Issues/Requests) <BR><BR>Pet heals need to be on-par with equivalent Beastlord heals HP-wise. The amount healed needs to be the same as beastlord heals, the cast time needs to be 3.75 seconds, and the recast time should be removed altogether.&nbsp;Higher level pet heals especially need a boost; in the time it takes to heal the pet, theres a high probability it is already dead. Also the amount currently healed is insufficient to&nbsp;equivalent level content (in Gates, for example, the 1200 HP healed from Planar Renewal is often less than one hit from random yard trash in Kod`Taz).</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT><BR>8) Revamp pet focus availability. (Pet Issues/Requests) <BR><BR>Add a Minion of Darkness focus in Tier 3 Planes of Power zones (ideal loot for mages would be First Sergeant's Insignia, and/or Orb of Infinite Terror) to help bridge the gap between equivalent Ornate-geared Magicians and Elemental-geared Mages, pet wise.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>Put the *Mancy focuses in the game. This will help bridge the gap between Ornate/Vex Thal-geared Magicians, Elemental-geared magicians, and Time-geared Magicians.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><BR>9) COH useable in more zones. (make CoTH available in all corpse summoning zones) <BR><BR></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times red; COLOR: 12pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><BR>10) Better utility in groups and raids </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>a) Summoned snare pet weapons,&nbsp;and new proc weapons for the pet</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>b) Castable root as a form of crowd control</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>c) AE malosinia</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>d) Group CoH</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>e) Cross-zone CoH (i think its being implemented)</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;f) Malos</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Roman?? New ?Times COLOR: 12pt; #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: red; COLOR: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0pt?></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana?><FONT color=#66ccff>Updated list 8/06/04</FONT></SPAN></P></DIV>
