			>
			<DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#00cc00 size=4><STRONG><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?COLOR: #00cc00;><FONT size=2><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff>Magician –&nbsp;<SPAN>Update scheduled for 10/22/04</SPAN></FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#00cc00 size=4><STRONG><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?COLOR: #00cc00;><FONT size=2><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff><SPAN></SPAN><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: New ?Times 12pt; Roman??><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff>Please note that there isn't any new development feedback in this update.</FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#00cc00 size=4><STRONG>Personal note to the developers:</STRONG></FONT> The #1 area that the Magician community would like to see a response from the developers is the return of the days when the mage could depend on <U>our pet</U> as a viable source of dps/defense for <U>the content </U>the we are fighting. Specifically this changed regarding pet scaling in PoP, GoD and OoW.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>Due to the fact that at lvl 58 and higher a magician could no longer count on the necessary dps/defensive abilities that <U>their pet</U> had provided them from lvls 4-57, there is a severe gap in our ability to be useful in a group or be a true soloing class beyond that level.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><STRONG><U>Please review item #1 on our list as the most important item to the mage community.</U></STRONG> This one area when resolved will fix 95% of all of the class balancing requests of the mage community. We have taken polls on the subject and roughly 70% of mages agree that fixing broken pets and improving our pets DPS/survivability(with pets being our only source of defense) is the only issue that truly matters.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>1.Improve pets - </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-<FONT color=#ffff00><U><STRONG>Damage ability</STRONG></U></FONT> Improve overall pet DPS for PoP, GoD, and OoW pets.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-<FONT color=#ffff00><STRONG><U>Survivability/Defense upgrade<BR></U></STRONG></FONT>a)Elemental immunities have been broken since they were changed&nbsp;(how pets resist spells) about 2 years ago,&nbsp;it is still broken. We should&nbsp;return the elementals immunity to their element (the same reason why mobs in Pofire are immune to our fire nukes).</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>b)Pet mitigation isn't terrible on baseline pets, but should scale much more based on what focus is being used. (A Tavici war is going to mitigate a TON better than an LDoN war, neglecting the massive hp and dps advantage he'll also have). All aspects of pets performance should scale the same way, not just boosts to hp, regen and dps.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-<STRONG><U><FONT color=#ffff00>Pet Utility</FONT></U></STRONG>- Restore four distinct and fully-functional pets. <BR>a)Rathe's Son and Child of Earth – Remove the proximity agro that root causes which makes our earth pet undesirable in groups and on raids.Possible solution:Re-code Earth Elemental Strike with proximity agro component removed.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>b)Fix our lvl 51 and higher fire pet - This pet has been broken for four years. It is so bad that mages can no longer use it. We have made repeated requests for fire pets to be fixed. We have presented several solutions, please address and complete this issue.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-<FONT color=#ffff00><STRONG><U>Upgrade our summoned focus items, pet armor and weapons</U></STRONG></FONT> - our brand new OoW pet weapons do no additional damage than the PoP era summoned weapons. (example spear of the deep/blade of the kedge). Summoned pet only items should have new procs like slow, snarelure and rune.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>2. Improve pet heals </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Shorter cast times and shorter recast times</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Have our pet focus (DPOC, MoD, MoE, MoDis, Ritual Summoning) also enhance pet heals</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Increase heal amount</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Give us a heal over time spell</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>3.Revamp pet focus, availability and drop rates </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red; 10pt;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG>
<DIV align=left><BR>-Give casual players and family guilds a way to obtain, quest or upgrade beyond the level of Summoner's boon. (MoD, MoE)</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>
<DIV align=left><BR>-Improve pet gains (especially DPS) with higher-level pet focus pieces. Pet focus should scale better with OoW era content.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>
<DIV align=left><BR><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>4. COTH utility </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Make CoTH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% rez zones. If a small area of the zone is necessary to have&nbsp;coth, corpse summon, druid 0% rez blocked for potential exploit reasons then just block that small area of the zone.</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Create a cross zone coth ability.</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><U>5. Update Rains </U></FONT><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red; 10pt;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Our high end OoW rains cannot be chain casted. Please remove the grey out blocker/locker on the casting times.</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Remove the innate resists on Rains, and retune the mana cost on many rains See <A href="http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911>http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html</FONT></A> for details.</DIV>
<DIV align=left><BR>6.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>7.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>8.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>9.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>10.defer to #1 Improve pets</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><FONT color=#999900><U><STRONG>Note to PvP correspondent/developers:</STRONG></U> <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>This item is on the PvP top 10 issues list, see here for details, </FONT></STRONG><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=5933" target=_blank><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=5933</FONT></STRONG></A></FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><U><FONT color=#999900></FONT></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Have pets be treated like PC’s instead of NPC’s for spell resists, damage, etc. See this link for detail: <A href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=16550&amp;highlight" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911>http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=16550&amp;highlight</FONT></A></DIV>
<DIV align=left><FONT color=#f0a911></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><FONT color=#999900><STRONG><U>Note: Items set to go live soon, but held up:</U> <FONT color=#ff0000>Submitted this suggestion to dev</FONT></STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><U><FONT color=#999900></FONT></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Making pet be able to survive invisibility - <FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red; ?Century Gothic?? mso-bidi-font-family: **SMURF**?COLOR:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: #cccccc; Verdana? **SMURF**?COLOR:><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Done</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></FONT><BR>-Targeted summons to hit live server. (possible interm solution make it just for pets until the code is developed for players to refuse?)</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<P><SPAN class=time_text></SPAN>&nbsp;</P></DIV>
