		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;<namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><date Month="12" Day="3" Year="2004"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Gothic?? ?Century fuchsia;>12/03/04</SPAN></date><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Gothic?? ?Century fuchsia;> - No new development feedback (LATE POST)</SPAN></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Updated mage list:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Dear developers,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Since July of this year the mage community has requested an answer to the following request:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>1. Improve overall pet DPS- </U><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>revised information being sent to development. (DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp; will be re-evaluated in the future)</FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><SPAN>On 7/9 we got this response:<FONT color=#ff0000><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><SPAN>On 7/26 we got this response:<FONT color=#ff0000 size=2><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><SPAN>On 8/6 we got this response:<FONT color=#ff0000 size=2><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><SPAN>On 8/27 we got this response: <FONT color=#ff0000 size=2><STRONG><SPAN><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000>Improvements will come with the Omens of War expansion</FONT></FONT></SPAN> </STRONG>
<P><STRONG><SPAN><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000>Further discussions on hold until after the Omens of War launch&nbsp;</FONT></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</STRONG></P></FONT>
<P>On 9/10 we got this response:<FONT color=#ff0000 size=2><SPAN><STRONG><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000>Improvements will come with the Omens of War expansion, and f</FONT></FONT><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000>urther discussions for improvment is on hold until after the Omens of War launch</FONT></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P></FONT>
<P><SPAN>We also modified&nbsp;the 9/10 request to specify:<SPAN>Damage ability (DPS upgrade, stats/hit consistency + accuracy /damage crits) - and got this response: <FONT color=#ff0000 size=2><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp; will be re-evaluated in the future </FONT></STRONG></SPAN></SPAN></P></FONT>
<P><SPAN>On 9/24 we got this response:<FONT color=#ff0000 size=2><STRONG>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp; will be re-evaluated in the future </STRONG></SPAN></P></FONT>
<P><SPAN>On 10/9 we got this response:<FONT color=#ff0000 size=2><STRONG>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp; will be re-evaluated in the future </STRONG></SPAN></P></FONT>
<P><SPAN>Recently I have read on the the mage community forums, increased&nbsp;exasperation concerning the pet DPS issue </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><A href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=18941&amp;highlight" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911>http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=18941&amp;highlight</FONT></A></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN>and recently polled the mages at 62% with&nbsp;all mages who responded being in favor of tossing out the entire top ten list in order to try to get some communication and action on this single request.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN>&nbsp;<A href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=18986&amp;postdays=0&amp;postorder=asc&amp;vote=viewresult" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911>http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=18986&amp;postdays=0&amp;postorder=asc&amp;vote=viewresult</FONT></A></SPAN></P><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>
<P><SPAN><FONT color=#00cc00><STRONG>Now that you have read the recent history of the mage pet dps "issue" would it be possible to please get some direct communication from&nbsp;the developers concerning their feelings on the subject and a possible gameplan/chat or forum type summit&nbsp;on what would be done about the situation? Please?</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P></FONT>
<P><SPAN>Most mages feel that the pet DPS issue is a class balance issue and mage pets&nbsp;should be getting&nbsp;a greater advantage in pet DPS than what we currently have compared to other "pet classes" in general due to&nbsp;NEC/BST superior utility. </SPAN><SPAN>Recently there have been changes to all pet classes, (invis, zoning, persistant minion, etc.&nbsp;but nothing specifaclly designed to resolve the mage situation. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN><SPAN>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN>The rest of the mages who responded to the poll&nbsp;feel that the remaining issues are minor compared to this PET DPS issue but I will list them anyway:</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-<FONT color=#ffff00><STRONG><U>Pet Survivability/Defense upgrade<BR></U></STRONG></FONT>a)Elemental immunities have been broken since they were changed&nbsp;(how pets resist spells) about 2 years ago,&nbsp;it is still broken. We should&nbsp;return the elementals immunity to their element (the same reason why mobs in Pofire are immune to our fire nukes).</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>b)Pet mitigation isn't terrible on baseline pets, but should scale much more based on what focus is being used. (A Tavici war is going to mitigate a TON better than an LDoN war, neglecting the massive hp and dps advantage he'll also have). All aspects of pets performance should scale the same way, not just boosts to hp, regen and dps.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-<STRONG><U><FONT color=#ffff00>Pet Utility</FONT></U></STRONG>- Restore four distinct and fully-functional pets.<BR>a)Rathe's Son and Child of Earth – Remove the proximity agro that root causes which makes our earth pet undesirable in groups and on raids.Possible solution:Re-code Earth Elemental Strike with proximity agro component removed.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>b)Fix our lvl 51 and higher fire pet - This pet has been broken for four years. It is so bad that mages can no longer use it. We have made repeated requests for fire pets to be fixed. We have presented several solutions, please address and complete this issue.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-<FONT color=#ffff00><STRONG><U>Upgrade our summoned&nbsp;pet armor</U></STRONG></FONT> -&nbsp;Our summoned pet armor was last upgraded at level 39. There should be additional pet armor upgrades at 50/60/70.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>2. Improve pet heals </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Pet heals should have shorter cast times and shorter recast times</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Have our pet focus (DPOC, MoD, MoE, MoDis, Ritual Summoning) also enhance pet heals</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>OR</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Increase HP heal amount</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>-Give us a heal over time spell</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>3.Revamp pet focus, availability and drop rates </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red; 10pt;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG>
<DIV align=left><BR>-Give casual players and family guilds a way to obtain, quest or upgrade beyond the level of Summoner's boon. (MoD, MoE) Currently the only way to get upgrades is to bring a well geared single group or a few casual geared groups into Riftseekers to get Minion of Darkness or get a full raid of casual players to get Minion of Eternity. The casual players really want a single group&nbsp;quest for both of the pet focus gear or augs.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>
<DIV align=left><BR>-Improve pet gains (especially DPS) with higher-level pet focus pieces. Pet focus should scale better with OoW era content.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV><SPAN class=postbody><SPAN><SPAN>
<DIV align=left><BR><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><STRONG><U>4. COTH utility </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Make CoTH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% rez zones. If a small area of the zone is necessary to have&nbsp;coth, corpse summon, druid 0% rez blocked for potential exploit reasons then just block that small area of the zone.</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Create a cross zone coth ability.</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><FONT color=#ff9900 size=4><U>5. Update Rains </U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;><SPAN COLOR: FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red; 10pt;><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><U><FONT color=#cc0000 size=4></FONT></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Our high end OoW rains cannot be chain casted. Please remove the grey out blocker/locker on the casting times.</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Remove the innate resists on Rains, and retune the mana cost on many rains See <A href="http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911>http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html</FONT></A> for details.</DIV>
<DIV align=left><BR>6.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>7.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>8.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>9.defer to #1 Improve pets<BR>10.defer to #1 Improve pets</DIV>
<DIV align=left>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left><FONT color=#999900><STRONG><U>Note:&nbsp;set to go live soon, but held up:</U> </STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV align=left><STRONG><U><FONT color=#999900></FONT></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV align=left>-Targeted summons to hit live server. <FONT color=#00cc00>(possible interm solution make it just for pets until the code is developed for players to refuse)</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></DIV></DIV></DIV>
