			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=3281#M3281">18</a> of 30
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 10700 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff00ff><FONT size=2><STRONG>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;<namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><date Year="2004" Day="3" Month="12"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Gothic?? ?Century fuchsia;>1/07/04</SPAN></date></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2><STRONG>1) Pet Upgrades - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR><BR>This is still our number one issue at the moment, most mages believe that pets have scaled very poorly over the expansions, especially in regards to what some melee have been seeing from PoP and above. This can be split into 2 sections.<BR><BR><FONT color=#32cd32>A) Improve Overall Pet DPS </FONT><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp; to be evaluated with the class Re-Envision process</STRONG></FONT><BR><BR><FONT color=#32cd32>B) Improve overall Pet Defense / Survivability </FONT></FONT></DIV><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR></DIV></FONT>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>2) Pet Focus Availability <FONT color=#ff0000>Revised item currently being discussed, new information passed along.</FONT></STRONG><BR><BR><BR><BR>There is a disctinct lack of available upgrades for pet focus items for the non-raiding mage past the Diamond Prism of Companionship, and for raiding mages past Jennu's Boots of Creation. I'll split the ideas into 2 sections.<BR><BR><FONT color=#32cd32>A) Non-Raiding Mages </FONT><BR><BR>Here's 3 ideas to give people who don't raid a shot at getting a better pet focus item. Currently the only 2 single groupable pet focus items, are summoners boon from lost dungeons of norrath, and minion of darkness from riftseekers, which not everyone is able or capable of fighting in.<BR><BR><FONT color=#ffd700>Option 1) Omens Crafted Augments</FONT> <BR><BR>Augments in Omens are a 2 stage, multi step process, firstly, you get a base augment, then use hydroabrasive and jewelcrafting to "cut" the gem to a better quality. <BR><BR>There are 3 different Qualities, and 2 different "groups" of base augment drops, namely: effects, and stats (effects use trean flies later, stats use slugworms). <BR><BR>After you have cut your gem, you can then add an effect to it via Smithing *and* either poisonmaking, or alchemy. This is done via item drops (slugworms, trean flies, discordant scoriae, etc) and vendor bought base components (which determine the actual effect the augment will have). This step also has 3 levels. <BR><BR>What I propose is an additional vendor bought rune that would be for pet focus effects, class limited to the 3 main pet classes. This would also have 3 levels, proposed to be: <BR><BR>XXX of Minor Companionship: Summoners Boon <BR>XXX of Companionship: Minion of Darkness <BR>XXX of Pure Companionship: Minion of Eternity <BR><BR><FONT color=#ffd700>Option 2) Better Selection of Drops </FONT><BR><BR>There's a lot of loot in the MPG group trials, and it is of *VERY* high quality, I believe a pet focus item could be squeezed in there somewhere, i'd suggest Ingenuity, since pet classes really shine there, it just seems to fit. Something with minion of eternity or ritual summoning wouldn't be out of character either, seeing as how there's a belt with Maelins Methodical Mind, previously a raid-only drop. <BR><BR>Perhaps the Fire DD focus ring from Wall of Slaughter could also be revamped to have minion of darkness, as well as be changed to MAG/NEC/BST. <BR><BR><FONT color=#ffd700>Option 3) Progressive Quest </FONT><BR><BR>A progressive quest along the lines of breakdown in communication or grand robe of the oracle. <BR><BR>A mix of the 2 quests would be the ideal solution, with 90% of it done solo camping various items, perhaps a few tradeskill combines, ground spawns, and 1 or 2 small group events. <BR><BR>The ideal reward would be an augment, as equipment upgrades tend to destroy useful effects on raw items, where as augments can be moved around easier. <BR><BR>I'd suggest the incremental rewards be something along the lines of: <BR><BR>30hp, 50mana, 9int, 9stam, misc resist, Summoners Boon <BR>45hp, 65mana, 12int, 12stam, misc resist, Minion of Darkness <BR>60hp, 80mana, 15int, 15stam, misc resist, Minion of Eternity<BR><BR><FONT color=#32cd32>B) Raiding Mages </FONT><BR><BR>While boots from qvic are very common, minion of discord and servant of chaos items are not. The only 2 options for minion of discord are from Zun in txevu, or from queen in riftseekers. Adding one more minion of discord item, possibly to MPG raid trials, would fix this issue for most. Adding a servant of chaos item to Ture or KTH in Anguish would also help.</FONT></P>
<P>-Add Servant of Chaos or Minion of Discord to the anguish quest boots, to be more in line with the qvic boots, and a viable upgrade.<BR></P><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR></DIV></FONT>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>3) Pet Focus Scaling - <FONT color=#ff0000>The way pet focus scales was smoothed out with the 12/15 update.&nbsp; I am sending the data below along.</FONT></STRONG><BR><BR><BR>Improve the way that the pet focus effects work on level 66+ pets, since the improvement they give has been largely diminished from what they did on the 61-65 pets.<BR><BR>There is a thread on the issue at the magetower boards </FONT><A href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=19275" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911 size=2>Here </FONT></A><FONT size=2>.<BR><BR>Here's one very good evaluation from the thread:<BR><BR></FONT>
<BLOCKQUOTE><BR><FONT size=2>
<HR>
Ithcyban of Veeshan wrote:<BR>
<HR>
<BR>To me, there are two things that need to scale with the pet. The first is DPS, which should scale comparably to the DPS of the caster, as influenced by focus effects and by AAs. The second is the ability to take damage, which is a combination of HP, mitigation, and avoidance, and should scale with the gear of the mage and their peers. <BR><BR>Looking at DPS, just what is the overall range and what are some possible intermediate values? Rather than looking at what pets did in the past, we should answer the question, <BR>"Do pets scale with mage nuking DPS as the mages progress?" <BR><BR>10% cleric spell haste assumed for all cases, as grouped performance seems to be more of interest to SOE than solo. DPS refers to theoretical maximum expected DPS, chain casting BoJ with no resists, no fizzles, and no time between casts. <BR><BR><BR>Baseline mage -- No damage-enhancing AAs seems in line with not having DPoC, given how easy it is to obtain for anyone in the 66-70 level range. Summoned focus pieces (20% DD, 15% time). <BR><BR>Baseline mage -- 405 DPS <BR><BR><BR>High-end GoD mage -- All applicable AAs; QD3, FoMM3, DF3 (HoF not included in any way, but probably should be in some fashion). 45% DD focus, 23% time focus. <BR><BR>High-end GoD mage -- 630 DPS <BR><BR><BR>High-end GoD mage casting DPS / Baseline mage casting DPS ~ 1.56 <BR><BR>MoD CoWind max hit / unfocused CoWind max hit ~ 1.16 <BR><BR>Something is way out of whack here. <BR><BR><BR>Ok, maybe SOE assumes that all mages have DPoC? Jump on me if I'm off, but here's a stab at a "casual" mage with DPoC in OoW. 25% fire focus, summoned 15% time focus, SCF3. From what I read, there still are a lot of mages in the 50-ish AA range, who are still working on "the basics" for AAs. SCF3 provides large gains, while the remaining crit-rate AAs do not. <BR><BR>DPoC mage -- 451 DPS <BR><BR>High-end GoD mage casting DPS / DPoC mage casting DPS ~ 1.40 <BR><BR>MoD CoWind max hit / DPoC CoWind max hit ~ 1.10 <BR><BR>Nope, that's not reasonable either. <BR><BR><BR><BR>So, let's try to define some intermediate steps between the mages without gear/AAs up through those with access to MoD. Access to focus effects is roughly related to when they appeared in as drops relative to the pet focus pieces. AAs are the tough one, but I took a stab at it (feel free to argue, but this is really just to get an idea of DPS potential). <BR><BR></FONT><PRE><BR><FONT size=2>Code:	<BR>                                              DPS Relative To: <BR>            DD   time  crit   QD    DF   DPS  Base  DPoC  Prev <BR>Baseline    20%   15%    0%              405  1     0.90   n/a <BR>DPoC        25%   15%   10%              451  1.11  1     1.11 <BR>MoDarkness  30%   18%   13%              496  1.22  1.10  1.10 <BR>MoEternity  35%   23%   16%              531  1.31  1.18  1.07 <BR>RitualSum   40%   23%   16%   10%        602  1.49  1.33  1.13 <BR>MoDiscord   45%   23%   16%   10%   25%  630  1.56  1.40  1.05	<BR></FONT></PRE><BR><BR><BR><FONT size=2>What do even steps look like? <BR><BR>(630/405)^(1/5) ~ 1.09 (per step, from unfocused) <BR>(630/451)^(1/4) ~ 1.09 (per step, from DPoC) <BR><BR><BR>So, as far as I'm concerned, pet DPS should be going up by about 40% over DPoC by the time you get to MoDiscord, to keep up with casting DPS, not the 10% total seen now. <BR><BR>The step from MoDiscord to Servant of Chaos should probably be at least the ratio of the Ancient to the non-Ancient OoW nuke, 537/498 right now, 8%, or arguably more with OoW pets as it is the current end-game pet focus. <BR><BR>This should be hard evidence that the failure of the pet focus pieces to appropriately increase pet DPS penalizes the scaling of mages against their DPS peers. <BR><BR><BR><BR>As far as HP goes, it is only one part of the equation. It certainly should scale similarly with gear potential from the various expansions, but also needs to include mitigation and avoidance to keep the pets on par with the mage's peers. 
<HR>
</FONT></BLOCKQUOTE><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR><BR><BR></DIV></FONT>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>4) Pet Heals and Buffs <SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated, the revised information has been passed along.</FONT></SPAN></STRONG><BR><BR><BR><BR><FONT color=#32cd32>A) Potency</FONT><BR><BR>Many mages believe that our heals are just too weak to meet todays demands from even increasing mob power, there are a few ways to solve this, but the best would be to provide 2 different magician spell healing lines, one for fast cast, fast healing, and one for slow cast, large healing.<BR><BR><BR><FONT color=#32cd32>B) Variety</FONT><BR><BR>Add a heal over time for our pets, something along the lines of breath of trushar<BR><BR>Add a protection of vie style buff for our pets to help with the defensive situation and improve solo ability / survivability </FONT></P><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR><BR></DIV></FONT>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>5) Update Rains <SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 10pt;><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? COLOR: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: red; 10pt;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed, new data below sent in.</FONT></SPAN></SPAN><BR></STRONG><BR><BR><BR>Remove the innate resists on Rains, and retune the mana cost on many rains See </FONT><A href="http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911 size=2>Xalmat's Rain Analysis </FONT></A><FONT size=2>for details.<BR><BR><BR><BR>As a rough guide, here as some requested changes:<BR><BR><BR><BR>1. Allow Improved Damage focii to work with Rains. <BR><BR><BR><BR>2. Remove the 20% resist rate on rains (consequently decrease rain wave damage by 20% to compensate) <BR><BR><BR><BR>3. Adjust the damage/mana ratio of rains to more properly fall in line with their corresponding DDs.<BR><BR></FONT></P><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR></DIV></FONT>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>6) Pet Item Summons - <FONT color=#ff0000>New, added with the 12/17/04 update, currently we do not have any development feedback.</FONT></STRONG></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT size=2>Belt should have 750hp AND worn haste, to both cut down on summons, and make the belt a respectable upgrade from it's predecessor</FONT> 
<LI><FONT size=2>Omens and PoP stun proc weapons added. </FONT>
<LI><FONT size=2>Omens and PoP lifetap and/or rune proc weapons. added </FONT></LI></UL><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR></DIV></FONT>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>7) Fire Pet - <SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></STRONG><BR><BR>There are many many many ideas on how to make this pet useful, as it stands now, it's used purely for novelty purposes, which leaves us with 3 pets. The wizard idea has not worked since the very start of kunark, as the pet simply cannot sustain the same level of DPS that our other pets can, it has a very dangerous spell line up, and runs out of mana very quickly.<BR><BR>There is a thread over on the Mage Compendium about fire pets, please take a quick look through to find an idea you like, there are many different ways to change the pet, all of which mentioned in this thread would make it more useful and viable than the current implementation.<BR><BR></FONT><A href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=15843" target=_blank><FONT color=#f0a911 size=2>http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=15843</FONT></A></P><FONT color=#f0a911 size=2>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV><BR><BR></DIV></FONT></FONT>
<P><STRONG>8) Omens 70 Spells <FONT color=#ff0000>Revised we currently do not have any new development feedback.&nbsp; Some of these issues may be evaluated as part of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></STRONG><FONT size=2><BR>-Star Strike modified to be doing 2350 damage for 485 mana would make it about 10% less DPS and 10% more efficient for a Spec:Conj mage as compared to a Spec:Evoc mage and BoJ. Such a change does not bring the mana efficiency out of line with the lower-level Blade Strike (less than 2% difference). <BR><BR>-Change Blade Strike to 2050 Damage and 455 mana. Thats an efficiency of 4.51 (Not a 70 spell, but if Star Strike changes, this should too). <BR><BR>-Circle of Fireskin: Change the Fire resist on this AND fireskin, to be slightly higher than it is now, currently it is the same as the PoP version of the spells, which is 45, upgrade to 62 would be great, 55 would be acceptable. <BR><BR>-Change Ancient: Nova Strike to Ancient: -Magic Sounding Bolt Name- <BR>3200 Damage, 700 Mana, Evocation, 7 Cast time. This will sit efficiency at 4.57, versus 4.4 of Bolt of Jerikor. <BR><BR>-Change Ancient: Nova Strike to be adjusted to be an appropriate boost, perhaps something like 2850 damage for 530 mana, for a 10% boost in DPS over BoJ and a 10% boost in efficiency over Star Strike. Giving the Ancient higher DPS and mana efficiency than any earlier spell has been the case with the previous Ancients.<BR></FONT><FONT size=2><FONT size=2>
<HR>

<P></P>
<DIV></FONT><FONT size=2><STRONG>9) COTH utility <SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed (resubmitted)&nbsp;This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></SPAN></STRONG><BR></FONT></DIV>
<UL>
<LI><FONT size=2>Make CoTH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% rez zones. If a small area of the zone is necessary to have coth, corpse summon, druid 0% rez blocked for potential exploit reasons then just block that small area of the zone.</FONT> 
<LI><FONT size=2>Create a cross zone coth ability.</FONT> 
<LI><FONT size=2>Add in higher levels / ways to improve CoTH, some ideas are:<BR>- Have an "elemental pact" style AA that negates the need for pearls. Clerics no longer require peridots, neither do necromancers, leading magician pearls as one of the very few remaining reagents to be purchased on a raid.<BR>-Simply remove the pearl reagent all together<BR>-Allow coth to work on *anyone* in the raid window, to save swapping out of groups, and making coth setup much easier.<BR>-Add an AA instant CoTH with a 72? minute reuse.</FONT></LI></UL><FONT size=2>
<P>
<HR>

<P></P>
<DIV></FONT><FONT size=2><STRONG>10) Bugged, Broken, and Useless - </STRONG>Buffs cannot be removed from pets to deal with stacking issues (e.g., ranger vs. pally buffs, conviction vs. symbol) <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed for all pet classes.</FONT></STRONG><BR></FONT></FONT></DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
