		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff00ff><FONT size=2><STRONG>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;3<namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><date Year="2004" Day="3" Month="12"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Gothic?? ?Century fuchsia;>/04/05</SPAN></date></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></FONT></DIV></FONT>
<DIV>Each item below has a more detailed explanation which will be posted by your Correspondent soon...</DIV><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>1.<SPAN></SPAN>Pet Upgrades - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT><BR></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>The poor scalability of our pets throughout the expansions.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Improve overall pet DPS - <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp; to be evaluated with the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Improver overall pet defense / survivability </FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>2.<SPAN></SPAN>Pet Focus Availability - <SPAN **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: red; Gothic?? ?Century><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><BR></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>Lack of available pet focus upgrades past Diamond Prism of Companionship (casual) or Jennu's Sandals of Creation (raider).</FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Non-raiding mage:</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>a. Add a DoN augment.<SPAN></SPAN>Minion of Darkness, 285 shards.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>b. Omens crafted augment.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>c. Better selection of drops (such as in a OoW single group trial).</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>d. Some type of progression quest.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Raiding mage:</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>a. Add servant of chaos to Anguish drops, such as OoW tier 2 boots.</FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>3.<SPAN></SPAN>Pet Focus Scaling - <SPAN **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: red; Gothic?? ?Century><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>Improve the way that the pet focus effects work on level 66+ pets, since the improvement they give has been largely diminished from what they did on the 61-65 pets.</FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>4.<SPAN></SPAN>Pet Heals and Buffs - <SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Verdana? red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>Better buffs and heals are needed to help a mage keep their pets alive as mob power continues to increase.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Heals.<SPAN></SPAN>Improve our existing line of heals</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>a. Fast cast, fast heal</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>b. Slow cast, large heal</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>c. Heal over time</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Buffs.<SPAN></SPAN>Add a Protection of Vie line of spells to help with the defensive situation and improve solo-ability / survivability.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>C. Heal Crits.<SPAN></SPAN>Give mages a chance to perform a critical heal based on nuke crit rate or AA.</FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>5.<SPAN></SPAN>Update Rains - <SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: Verdana? 10pt;><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: Verdana? red; 10pt;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>Remove the innate resists on Rains and retune the mana cost to be more in line with their corresponding DDs.<SPAN></SPAN>Also consider allowing improved damage foci to affect rains.</FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>6.<SPAN></SPAN>Omens Spells - <FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: red; Gothic?? ?Century><SPAN **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: red; Gothic?? ?Century><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.&nbsp; </FONT></SPAN>Some of these issues may be evaluated as part of the class Re-Envision process.</SPAN></FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>Upgrade Omens spells to be more balanced in terms of damage : mana.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Star Strike.<SPAN></SPAN>2350 dmg, 485 mana</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Blade Strike.<SPAN></SPAN>2050 dmg, 455 mana</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>C. Ancient:<SPAN></SPAN>Nova Strike.<SPAN></SPAN>2850 dmg, 530 mana</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>D. Circle of Fireskin and Fireskin.<SPAN></SPAN>Increase the the FR component from 45 to 55-62.</FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>7.<SPAN></SPAN>Pet Item summons - <FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN **SMURF**?COLOR: mso-bidi-font-family: red; Gothic?? ?Century>Currently being discussed</SPAN>.</FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Belt should have 750hp AND worn haste.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Omens and PoP proc upgrades:<SPAN></SPAN>stun, lifetap and / or rune</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>8.<SPAN></SPAN>Fire Pet - <SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN><BR></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>Currently many ideas on how to make this pet useful listed on the magetower.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Fire has weak melee and weak defense.<SPAN></SPAN>Pet roots self and starts chain nuking a chromatic -50 DD at the mob until mob dies, runs out of mana, or pet dies.<SPAN></SPAN>DPS should be greater than air pet, but less than water pet.<SPAN></SPAN>Damage scales with level of pet focus.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Upgraded version of our pre-50 level fire pets.<SPAN></SPAN>Weak offense and defense, but a large self damage shield that stacks with existing mage DS.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>C. Lesser version of air pet but with some unique group feature such as:<SPAN></SPAN>bard song (+ mana regen, + hp regen or nuke boosting song), cleric ward, buff that adds procs to melees.</FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>9. CotH utility - <SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.&nbsp; This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Make CotH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% zones.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Create a cross-zone CotH ability.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>C. Create an "elemental pact" style AA that negates the need for stacks of pearls.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>D. Allow CotH to work on anyone within a raid.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>E. Add an instant CotH AA with appropriate reuse timer.</FONT></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2><STRONG>10.<SPAN></SPAN>Bugged, Broken, and Useless</STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN><FONT size=2>A. Buffs cannot be removed from pets to deal with stacking issues. <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed for all pet classes.</FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>B. Allow Mod rods (3 charge and 1 charge version) to be used in potion belt. <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.</FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN><SPAN><FONT size=2>C. Add the nifty graphic to Mod rods as a visual cue as to when the reuse timer is up. <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.</FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P></DIV></FONT></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							*************************************************<br>Ashlanne Barefoot<br>Community Relations Coordinator<br>Norrath, where I kick off my shoes and run in bare feet.<br><b><a href="http://stationforums.station.sony.com/communitysoe/ "><font color="red">Check out the Station Forums!</font></a>
							</div>
								
