<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=3512#M3512">21</a> of 30
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 9691 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff00ff><FONT size=2><STRONG>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;4<namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><date Month="12" Day="3" Year="2004"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Gothic?? ?Century fuchsia;>/01/05</SPAN></date></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></FONT></DIV><FONT size=2>
<DIV><BR><STRONG>1.&nbsp; Pet Upgrades / Pet Focus Scaling</STRONG> - The poor scalability of our pets throughout the expansions.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;A. Improve overall pet DPS&nbsp; - <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp; to be evaluated with part #2 of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; B. Improve overall pet defense / survivability&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; C. Improve the way that the pet focus effects work on level 66+ pets, since the improvement they give has <BR>been largely diminished from what they did on the 61-65 pets.&nbsp;&nbsp; This especially applies to the scale up from <BR>Minion of Eternity --&gt; Ritual Summoning --&gt; Minion of Discord --&gt; Servant of Chaos (a very big disappointment <BR>in terms of overall pet power). </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>2.&nbsp; Omens Spells -</STRONG> Upgarde Omens spells to be more balance in terms of damage : mana cost. <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated, some of these may be addressed with the Re-Envision Process</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A.&nbsp; Blade Strike:&nbsp; 2000 dmg, sama mana, 4.5 efficiency<BR>&nbsp; B.&nbsp; Star Strike:&nbsp; 2300 dmg, sama mana, 4.7 efficiency<BR>&nbsp; C.&nbsp; Ancient:&nbsp; Nova Strike:&nbsp; 2600 dmg, same mana, 5.0 efficiency<BR>&nbsp; D.&nbsp; Circle of Fireskin and Fireskin.Increase the the FR component from 45 to 55-62.<BR>&nbsp; E.&nbsp; Consider making all nukes Conjuration based (i.e. bolts, rains, AEs and burning sand line)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>3.&nbsp; Fire Pet -</STRONG> Currently many ideas on how to make this pet useful listed on the magetower.&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG> </FONT><BR>&nbsp; A. Fire has weak melee and weak defense.Pet roots self and starts chain nuking a chromatic -50 DD at the <BR>mob until mob dies, runs out of mana, or pet dies.DPS should be equalto or greater than air pet, but less than water <BR>pet.Damage scales with level of pet focus.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; B. Upgraded version of our pre-50 level fire pets.Weak offense and defense, but a large self damage shield <BR>that stacks with existing mage DS.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; C. Lesser version of air pet but with some unique group feature such as:bard song (+ mana regen, + hp <BR>regen or nuke boosting song), cleric ward, buff that adds procs to melees.<BR>&nbsp; D.&nbsp; Probably the best suggestion was to make the old Fire pet model scale up through lvl 60, and then make the<BR>subsequent lvl 61+ fire pets behave more like a Servant of Ro-- which chain nukes a chromatic nuke at the DPS ~ to<BR>air pet (scales with pet focus).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>4.&nbsp; Pet Buffs -</STRONG> Better buffs are needed to help a mage keep their pets alive as mob power continues to <BR>increase.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A. Buffs.&nbsp; Add a Protection of Vie line of spells to help with the defensive situation and improve solo-ability / <BR>survivability.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; B. Heal Crits.&nbsp; Give mages a chance to perform a critical heal based on nuke crit rate or AA.&nbsp; <BR><STRONG>&nbsp;<BR>5.&nbsp; Pet Item summons - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A. Omens and PoP proc upgrades:stun, lifetap and / or rune <BR>&nbsp; B. Consider a shield / weapon combo for increase defensibility.&nbsp; Shield would have a large number of <BR>hitpoint, but would also have +avoidance or +shielding to help it mitigate damage.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>6.&nbsp; Mod Rods - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A. Allow Mod rods (3 charge and 1 charge version) to be used in potion belt, and add the nifty graphic to Mod <BR>rods as a visual cue as to when the reuse timer is up.<BR>&nbsp; B. Consider an upgrade to current Mod Rod.&nbsp; More charges or more mana / click (at the cost of more <BR>health).&nbsp; Also consider adding +endurance component.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>7. CotH utility - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.&nbsp; This may be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A. Make CotH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% zones.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; B. Create a cross-zone CotH ability.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; C. Create an "elemental pact" style AA that negates the need for stacks of pearls.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; D. Allow CotH to work on anyone within a raid.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; E. Add an instant CotH AA with appropriate reuse timer.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>8.&nbsp; Fix Frenzied Burnout - <FONT color=#ff0000>New</FONT></STRONG><BR>Remove the +str component so it can stack with Talisman / STR of Daiku.&nbsp; <BR>Shorten the recast to 9 min like our Servant of Ro.&nbsp; Consider increasing the duration to 1 minute.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>9.&nbsp; Utility - <FONT color=#ff0000>New</FONT></STRONG><BR>Consider making a siphon line that is group buff (like BST SA or Necro Mind Wrack).&nbsp; Depending on the spell<BR>it could tap the pet and provide a number of group benefits:&nbsp; melee mitigation, atk buff, mana regen, proc, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>10.&nbsp; Younger mages -</STRONG>&nbsp; consider extending the Summoned Orb line of spells to younger mages.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>New</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>--<BR>Fixed (assuming changes are made as listed in the first round of class re-envisionment)<BR>-Pet Focus Availability&nbsp; <BR>-Pet Heals (increasing heal amount, decrease cast time)<BR>-Update Rains<BR>-Buffs can be clicked off of pets<BR>-Including new pet packs to reduce number of summons.&nbsp; Also allowing us to summon directly to a player.</FONT></DIV></FONT></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							*************************************************<br>Ashlanne Barefoot<br>Community Relations Coordinator<br>Norrath, where I kick off my shoes and run in bare feet.<br><b><a href="http://stationforums.station.sony.com/communitysoe/ "><font color="red">Check out the Station Forums!</font></a>
							</div>
								
