		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff00ff><FONT size=2><STRONG>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;5<namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><date Month="12" Day="3" Year="2004"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?COLOR: fuchsia;>/06/05</SPAN></date></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></FONT></DIV><FONT size=2>
<DIV>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>1.&nbsp; Pet Upgrades / Pet Focus Scaling</STRONG> - The poor scalability of our pets throughout the expansions.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp;A. Improve overall pet DPS&nbsp;&nbsp;<STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp;is being evaluated with part #2 of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp;B. Improve overall pet defense / survivability&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;C. Improve the way that the pet focus effects work on level 66+ pets, since the improvement they give has<BR>been largely diminished from what they did on the 61-65 pets.&nbsp;&nbsp; This especially applies to the scale up from<BR>Minion of Eternity ? Ritual Summoning ? Minion of Discord ? Servant of Chaos (a very big disappointment<BR>in terms of overall pet power). </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>2.&nbsp; Omens Spells -</STRONG> Upgarde Omens spells to be more balance in terms of damage : mana cost.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated, some of these may be addressed with the Re-Envision Process</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A.&nbsp; Ancient:&nbsp; Nova Strike:&nbsp; less dps than bolt of jerikor, but a nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost (2650 dmg, 576 mana<SPAN class=mediumtext1><SPAN>)</SPAN></SPAN><BR>&nbsp; B.&nbsp; Star Strike:&nbsp; nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost, but less efficient than ancient (<SPAN class=mediumtext1><SPAN>2377 dmg, 525 mana)</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN class=mediumtext1><SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><BR>&nbsp; C.&nbsp; Circle of Fireskin and Fireskin.Increase the the FR component from 45 to 55-62.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;D.&nbsp; Consider making all nukes the same specialization subset (i.e. bolts, rains, AEs and burning sand line)</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>3.&nbsp; Fire Pet -</STRONG> Currently many ideas on how to make this pet useful listed on the magetower.&nbsp;<FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG>&nbsp;</FONT><BR>&nbsp;A. Fire has weak melee and weak defense.Pet roots self and starts chain nuking a chromatic -50 DD at the<BR>mob until mob dies, runs out of mana, or pet dies.DPS should be greater than air pet, but less than water<BR>pet.Damage scales with level of pet focus.&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;B. Upgraded version of our pre-50 level fire pets.Weak offense and defense, but a large self damage shield<BR>that stacks with existing mage DS.&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;C. Lesser version of air pet but with some unique group feature such as:bard song (+ mana regen, + hp<BR>regen or nuke boosting song), cleric ward, buff that adds procs to melees.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>4.&nbsp; Pet Buffs -</STRONG> Better buffs are needed to help a mage keep their pets alive as mob power continues to<BR>increase.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp;A. Buffs.&nbsp; Add a Protection of Vie line of spells to help with the defensive situation and improve solo-ability /<BR>survivability.&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;B. Heal Crits.&nbsp; Give mages a chance to perform a critical heal based on nuke crit rate or AA.&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;<BR><STRONG>5.&nbsp; Pet Item summons</STRONG> <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp;A. Omens and PoP proc upgrades:stun, lifetap and / or rune<BR>&nbsp;B. Consider a shield / weapon combo for increase defensibility.&nbsp; Shield would have a large number of<BR>hitpoint, but would also have +avoidance or +shielding to help it mitigate damage. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>6. Mod Rods</STRONG> <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG><BR>A. Allow Mod rods (3 charge and 1 charge version) to be used in potion belt, and add the nifty graphic to Mod<BR>rods as a visual cue as to when the reuse timer is up.<BR>B. Consider an upgrade to current Mod Rod. More charges or more mana / click (at the cost of more<BR>health). Also consider adding +endurance component. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>7. CotH utility -</STRONG>&nbsp;<STRONG> <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.&nbsp; This may be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><BR>A. Make CotH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% zones.<BR>B. Create a cross-zone CotH ability.<BR>C. Create an "elemental pact" style AA that negates the need for stacks of pearls.<BR>D. Allow CotH to work on anyone within a raid.<BR>E. Add an instant CotH AA with appropriate reuse timer. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>8. Fix Frenzied Burnout</STRONG> <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Added to the list on 4/1/05, no development feedback yet.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN><BR>Remove the +str component so it can stack with Talisman / STR of Daiku.<BR>Shorten the recast to 9 min like our Servant of Ro. Consider increasing the duration to 1 minute. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>9. Utility</STRONG> - <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Added to the list on 4/1/05, no development feedback yet.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN><BR>-Consider making a siphon line that is group buff (like BST SA or Necro Mind Wrack). Depending on the spell<BR>it could tap the pet and provide a number of group benefits: melee mitigation, atk buff, mana regen, proc, etc.<BR>-Consider making %dmg modifier (lions strength, elemental fury, champion) stack on pets.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><STRONG>10. Younger mages -</STRONG> consider extending the Summoned Orb line of spells to younger mages.&nbsp; <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Added to the list on 4/1/05, no development feedback yet.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>--</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2>Fixed (assuming changes are made as listed in the first round of class re-envisionment) <BR>-Pet Focus Availability (MoD focus to be added to DoN.. /cheer and there was much rejoicing)<BR>-Pet Heals (/cheer and there was much rejoicing)<BR>-Update Rains (/cheer and there was much rejoicing)<BR>-Buffs can be clicked off of pets<BR>-Targetable summons<BR>-Including new pet packs to reduce number of summons.&nbsp; Also allowing us to summon directly to a player.</FONT></P></DIV></FONT></FONT></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							*************************************************<br>Ashlanne Barefoot<br>Community Relations Coordinator<br>Norrath, where I kick off my shoes and run in bare feet.<br><b><a href="http://stationforums.station.sony.com/communitysoe/ "><font color="red">Check out the Station Forums!</font></a>
							</div>
								
