Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=3761#M3761">23</a> of 30
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 9112 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;7<namespace prefix = st1 ><date Month="12" Day="3" Year="2004"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **SMURF**?COLOR: Gothic?? ?Century fuchsia;>/05/05</SPAN></date></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>1. Pet Upgrades / Pet Focus Scaling - The poor scalability of our pets throughout the expansions.&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated</STRONG></FONT><BR></DIV>
<DIV>A. Improve overall pet DPS <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS for all classes (and pets) is being evaluated with part #2 of the class Re-Envision process DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp;is being evaluated with part #2 of the class Re-Envision process<BR></FONT></STRONG>B. Improve overall pet defense / survivability</DIV>
<DIV>C. Improve the way that the pet focus effects work on level 66+ pets, since the improvement they give has been largely diminished from what they did</DIV>
<DIV>on the 61-65 pets. This especially applies to the scale up from Minion of Eternity&nbsp;-&gt; Ritual Summoning -&gt; Minion of Discord -&gt; Servant of Chaos (a</DIV>
<DIV>very big disappointment in terms of overall pet power).</DIV>
<DIV><BR>2. Omens Spells - Upgarde Omens spells to be more balance in terms of damage : mana cost <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated, some of these may be addressed with the Re-Envision Process</STRONG>.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>A. Ancient: Nova Strike: less dps than bolt of jerikor, but a nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost</DIV>
<DIV>B. Star Strike: nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost, but less efficient than ancient</DIV>
<DIV>C. Circle of Fireskin and Fireskin.Increase the the FR component from 45 to 55-62.</DIV>
<DIV>D. Consider making all nukes the same specialization subset (i.e. bolts, rains, AEs and burning sand line)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Fire Pet - Currently many ideas on how to make this pet useful listed on the magetower. <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG>&nbsp;</FONT><BR></DIV>
<DIV>A. The best suggestion (which seems to have support) is the following:&nbsp; lvl 50-60 fire pets follow the same model as the lvl 1-49 fire pets (low hp, high</DIV>
<DIV>damage shield).&nbsp; The lvl 63+ fire pets should be a nuking only pet:&nbsp; it roots to where it is when it is told to attack and then casts a chromatic nuke at</DIV>
<DIV>the mob until the told to stop.&nbsp; The dps of the fire pet should be somehwere around air pet-water pet with nukes only, it can't really attack and</DIV>
<DIV>certainly can't mitigate damage..&nbsp; This second version is more of a raid pet (useful against AE rampage, etc).<BR></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Pet Buffs - Better buffs are needed to help a mage keep their pets alive as mob power continues to increase. <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR></DIV>
<DIV>A. Heal Crits. Give mages a chance to perform a critical heal based on nuke crit rate or AA.</DIV>
<DIV>B. Buffs. Add a Protection of Vie line of spells to help with the defensive situation and improve solo-ability / survivability.<BR></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5. Pet Item summons <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR></DIV>
<DIV>A. Omens and PoP proc upgrades:stun, lifetap, and / or rune</DIV>
<DIV>B. Consider a shield / weapon combo for increase defensibility. Shield would have a large number of hitpoint, but would also have +avoidance or</DIV>
<DIV>+shielding to help it mitigate damage.</DIV>
<DIV>C. Targetable summons (was told this was to be part of re-envisioning, just adding back on the list).</DIV>
<DIV>D. Pet packs to reduce the number of items being summoned (was told this was to be part of re-envisioning, just adding back on the list).</DIV>
<DIV><BR>6. Mod Rods <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG><BR></DIV>
<DIV>A. Consider an upgrade to current Mod Rod. More charges or more mana / click (at the cost of more health).<BR></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>7. CotH utility - thank you for zonewide /invite <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.&nbsp; This may be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>A. Make CotH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% zones.</DIV>
<DIV>B. Create a cross-zone CotH ability.</DIV>
<DIV>C. Create an "elemental pact" style AA that negates the need for stacks of pearls.</DIV>
<DIV>D. Allow CotH to work on anyone within a raid.</DIV>
<DIV>E. Add an instant CotH AA with appropriate reuse timer.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>8. Utility <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed as part of class re-envision</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN><BR><BR></DIV>
<DIV>-Consider making a siphon line that is group buff (like BST SA or Necro Mind Wrack). Depending on the spell it could tap the pet and provide a</DIV>
<DIV>number of group benefits: melee mitigation, atk buff, mana regen, proc, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>-Consider making %dmg modifier (lions strength, elemental fury, champion) stack on pets.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9. Younger mages - consider extending the Summoned Orb line of spells to younger mages.&nbsp; <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10. Remove buffs with click from pets (was told this was to be part of re-envisioning, just adding back on the list).&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Re-Addition - This is planned as part of class re-envision</STRONG></FONT></DIV><p>Message Edited by Ashlanne on <span class=date_text>07-06-2005</span> <span class=time_text>12:23 PM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
