		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff00ff><FONT size=2><STRONG>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;7<namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com<img 
src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-surprised.gif' width=16 height=16 
border=0>ffice:smarttags" ><date Year="2004" Day="3" Month="12"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?COLOR: fuchsia;>/05/05 - No changes at this time.</SPAN></date></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></FONT></DIV><FONT size=2>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2><EM>The mage top "10" continues to have the theme of pets / dps.&nbsp; Casual mages are worried about their pets not being able to tank sufficently.&nbsp; Raiding mages are concered with the pet scaling (or lack thereof) with the higher end foci.&nbsp; Both camps are worried about dps output of said pets.&nbsp; The changes to pet heals are absolutely phenomenal.</EM></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>1.&nbsp; Pet Upgrades / Pet Focus Scaling - The poor scalability of our pets throughout the expansions.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A. Improve overall pet DPS&nbsp;&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp;is being evaluated with part #2 of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; B. Improve overall pet defense / survivability&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; C. Improve the way that the pet focus effects work on level 66+ pets, since the improvement they give has <BR>been largely diminished from what they did on the 61-65 pets.&nbsp;&nbsp; This especially applies to the scale up from <BR>Minion of Eternity ? Ritual Summoning ? Minion of Discord ? Servant of Chaos (a very big disappointment <BR>in terms of overall pet power). </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>2.&nbsp; Omens Spells - Upgarde Omens spells to be more balance in terms of damage : mana cost.&nbsp;<STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated, some of these may be addressed with the Re-Envision Process</FONT></STRONG><BR><BR>&nbsp; A.&nbsp; Ancient:&nbsp; Nova Strike:&nbsp; less dps than bolt of jerikor, but a nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost<BR>&nbsp; B.&nbsp; Star Strike:&nbsp; nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost, but less efficient than ancient<BR>&nbsp; C.&nbsp; Circle of Fireskin and Fireskin.Increase the the FR component from 45 to 55-62.<BR>&nbsp; D.&nbsp; Consider making all nukes the same specialization subset (i.e. bolts, rains, AEs and burning sand line)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>3.&nbsp; Fire Pet - Currently many ideas on how to make this pet useful listed on the magetower.&nbsp;<FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG>&nbsp;</FONT><BR><BR>&nbsp; A. Fire has weak melee and weak defense.Pet roots self and starts chain nuking a chromatic -50 DD at the <BR>mob until mob dies, runs out of mana, or pet dies.DPS should be greater than air pet, but less than water <BR>pet.Damage scales with level of pet focus.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; B. Upgraded version of our pre-50 level fire pets.Weak offense and defense, but a large self damage shield <BR>that stacks with existing mage DS.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; C. Lesser version of air pet but with some unique group feature such as:bard song (+ mana regen, + hp <BR>regen or nuke boosting song), cleric ward, buff that adds procs to melees.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>4.&nbsp; Pet Buffs - Better buffs are needed to help a mage keep their pets alive as mob power continues to <BR>increase.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>&nbsp; A. Buffs.&nbsp; Add a Protection of Vie line of spells to help with the defensive situation and improve solo-ability / <BR>survivability.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp; B. Heal Crits.&nbsp; Give mages a chance to perform a critical heal based on nuke crit rate or AA.&nbsp; <BR>&nbsp;<BR>5.&nbsp; Pet Item summons <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR><BR>&nbsp; A. Omens and PoP proc upgrades:stun, lifetap and / or rune <BR>&nbsp; B. Consider a shield / weapon combo for increase defensibility.&nbsp; Shield would have a large number of <BR>hitpoint, but would also have +avoidance or +shielding to help it mitigate damage. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>6. Mod Rods <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG><BR><BR>A. Allow Mod rods (3 charge and 1 charge version) to be used in potion belt, and add the nifty graphic to Mod <BR>rods as a visual cue as to when the reuse timer is up. <BR>B. Consider an upgrade to current Mod Rod. More charges or more mana / click (at the cost of more <BR>health). Also consider adding +endurance component. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>7. CotH utility - <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.&nbsp; This may be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><BR><BR>A. Make CotH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% zones. <BR>B. Create a cross-zone CotH ability. <BR>C. Create an "elemental pact" style AA that negates the need for stacks of pearls. <BR>D. Allow CotH to work on anyone within a raid. <BR>E. Add an instant CotH AA with appropriate reuse timer. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>8. Fix Frenzied Burnout <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>This issue is currently being evaluated by Rashere.&nbsp; Please leave your feedback in the post he started on the </FONT></STRONG><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=3683" target=_blank><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Magician board.</FONT></STRONG><BR></A>I know this is being visited ...</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>Remove the +str component so it can stack with Talisman / STR of Daiku. <BR>Shorten the recast to 9 min like our Servant of Ro. Consider increasing the duration to 1 minute. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>9. Utility - <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed as part of class re-envision</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN><BR><BR>-Consider making a siphon line that is group buff (like BST SA or Necro Mind Wrack). Depending on the spell <BR>it could tap the pet and provide a number of group benefits: melee mitigation, atk buff, mana regen, proc, etc. <BR>-Consider making %dmg modifier (lions strength, elemental fury, champion) stack on pets.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>10. Younger mages - consider extending the Summoned Orb line of spells to younger mages. <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>Fixed (assuming changes are made as listed in the first round of class re-envisionment) <BR>-Pet Focus Availability (MoD focus to be added to DoN.. /cheer and there was much rejoicing)<BR>-Pet Heals (/cheer and there was much rejoicing) <BR>-Update Rains (/cheer and there was much rejoicing)<BR>-Buffs can be clicked off of pets <BR>-Targetable summons<BR>-Including new pet packs to reduce number of summons.&nbsp; Also allowing us to summon directly to a player.</FONT></FONT></FONT></DIV></DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
