		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#ff00ff>Magician - List Update scheduled for&nbsp;7<namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com<img 
src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-surprised.gif' width=16 height=16 
border=0>ffice:smarttags" ><date Month="12" Day="3" Year="2004"><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?COLOR: fuchsia;>/08/05</SPAN></date></FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>1. Pet DPS Upgrades <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>A. Improve overall pet DPS DPS for all classes (and pets) <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>DPS for all classes (and pets) is being evaluated with part #2 of the class Re-Envision process DPS for all classes (and pets)&nbsp;is being evaluated with part #2 of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><BR>B. Improve overall pet defense / survivability <BR>C.&nbsp;Fix elemental agility.&nbsp;</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>D.&nbsp;Improve perfomance of Elemental Fury (crits).&nbsp; 25 AA for a 3-5 dps increase with the highest focused pet seems low.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>2. Omens Spells - Upgarde Omens spells to be more balance in terms of damage : mana cost. <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being evaluated, some of these may be addressed with the Re-Envision Process</STRONG>.</FONT><BR>A. Ancient: Nova Strike: less dps than bolt of jerikor, but a nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost <BR>B. Star Strike: nice balance of fire dmg to mana cost, but less efficient than ancient <BR>C. Circle of Fireskin and Fireskin.&nbsp; Increase the the FR component from 45 to 55-62. <BR>D. Consider making all nukes the same specialization subset (i.e. bolts, rains, AEs and burning sand line) </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>3. Fire Pet - Currently many ideas on how to make this pet useful listed on the magetower. <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG><BR>A. The best suggestion (which seems to have support) is the following: lvl 50-60 fire pets follow the same model as the lvl 1-49 fire pets (low hp, high</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>damage shield). The lvl 63+ fire pets should be a nuking only pet: it roots to where it is when it is told to attack and then casts a chromatic nuke at </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>the mob until the told to stop. The dps of the fire pet should be somehwere around air pet-water pet with nukes only, it can't really attack and </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>certainly can't mitigate damage.. This second version is more of a raid pet (useful against AE rampage, etc). </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>4. Mod Rods <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG><BR></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>- Consider a raid level mod rod&nbsp;that would be usable for CRs&nbsp;to get buffing classes&nbsp;FoM faster.&nbsp; One possibility would be to but a counter on the player when the Conversion Rod is clicked:&nbsp; -300 hp / tick, +300 mana / tick, silence, duration 10 ticks.&nbsp; So you can recover up to 3k mana,&nbsp;at the cost of 3k hp and&nbsp;the loss&nbsp;spellcasting ability.&nbsp; A player could click it off early (in case of emergency), but wouldn't gain the full benefit of the mana regen.&nbsp;</FONT></DIV></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>5. Pet Buffs - Better buffs are needed to help a mage keep their pets alive as mob power continues to increase.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>A. Heal Crits. Give mages a chance to perform a critical heal based on nuke crit rate or AA. <BR>B. Buffs. Add a Protection of Vie line of spells to help with the defensive situation and improve solo-ability / survivability. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>6. Pet Item summons <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></STRONG><BR>A. Omens and PoP proc upgrades: lifetap or vie type of proc (35%&nbsp;/ 500hp for example)<BR>B. Consider a shield / weapon combo for increase defensibility. Shield would have a large number of hitpoint, but would also have +avoidance or <BR>+shielding to help it mitigate damage. <BR>C. Targetable summons (was told this was to be part of re-envisioning, just adding back on the list). <BR>D. Pet packs to reduce the number of items being summoned (was told this was to be part of re-envisioning, just adding back on the list). </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>7. CotH utility - thank you for zonewide /invite <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed.&nbsp; This may be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG><BR>A. Make CotH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% zones. <BR>B. Create a cross-zone CotH ability. <BR>C. Create an "elemental pact" style AA that negates the need for stacks of pearls. <BR>D. Allow CotH to work on anyone within a raid. <BR>E. Add an instant CotH AA with appropriate reuse timer. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>8. Utility <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed as part of class re-envision</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN><BR>A. Consider making a siphon line that is group buff (like BST SA or Necro Mind Wrack). Depending on the spell it could tap the pet and provide a <BR>number of group benefits: melee mitigation, atk buff, mana regen, proc, etc. <BR>B. Consider making %dmg modifier (lions strength, elemental fury, champion) stack on pets. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>9. Younger mages - consider extending the Summoned Orb line of spells to younger mages. <SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>10. Remove buffs with click from pets <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Re-Addition - This is planned as part of class re-envision</FONT></STRONG></FONT></DIV></DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							*************************************************<br>Ashlanne Barefoot<br>Community Relations Coordinator<br>Norrath, where I kick off my shoes and run in bare feet.<br><b><a href="http://stationforums.station.sony.com/communitysoe/ "><font color="red">Check out the Station Forums!</font></a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
